&lt;p&gt;Thousands of people gathered in Washington DC's National Mall and other cities across the United States to protest against President Donald Trump's policies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &quot;Hands Off!&quot; protests were organised at over 1,200 locations in all 50 states across the country by more than 150 groups including civil rights organisations, labour unions, LGBTQ+ advocates, veterans and election activists. Associated Press reported that there were no immediate arrests and the demonstrations seemed peaceful.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The demonstrators protested against various policies of Trump and Elon Musk including government downsizing, the economy, immigration and human rights. On the West Coast, protestors held signs with slogans reading &quot;Fight the oligarchy.&quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
